Contractors

ChampionX has written procedures and policies regarding the use of contractors in and around covered processes.  These procedures are used to confirm that contractor employees have been adequately trained, have safe work practices, and have been informed of all potential hazards.



Employee Participation

ChampionX encourages all employees to actively participate in the development and use of ChampionX accidental release prevention programs.



Compliance Audits

ChampionX has a program in place to evaluate compliance with the RMP rule every three years to verify that the procedures and practices are adequate and are being followed. 



1.5    Prevention Program

 ChampionX has implemented the following prevention program release mitigation steps:

?    Dikes around chemical storage tanks;

?    Foam/Water sprinkler systems throughout the production buildings;

?    Foam systems in flammable product and raw material warehouses;

?    Emergency communication and alarm system;

?    Firewater monitors and fire hydrants;

?    Fire extinguishers;

?    Dedicated firewater system with diesel engine backup;

?    Over one million gallons of firewater stored on-site;

?    Monitoring of on-site emergency response team;

?    Reduction in the surface area of diked areas around regulated chemicals; 

?    Continuous emissions monitoring from the thermal oxidizers; and

?    Containment area for the unloading of tank trucks of epichlorohydrin and cyclohexylamine.



In addition, the following chemical-specific steps have been implemented:

?    Control emissions from production operations that handle RMP toxic chemicals.

?    Vapor return for unloading of RMP toxic chemicals to storage tanks.



These individual elements of the ChampionX prevention program work together to help prevent accidental chemical releases.



